UNITED STATES of America ex rel. Oscar MANNISTO, Relator-Appellant, v. Rudolph REIMER, Commissioner of Immigration, Ellis Island, New York Harbor, Respondent-Appellee. No. 453. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 20, 1935. Fannie Horovitz, of New York City (Samuel Friedlander, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Martin Conboy, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Edward J. Ennis, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
